\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bkj1665702660842.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bkj1665702660842.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bkj1665702660842.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bkj1665702660842\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger next\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Trigger that responds to a request for the next field in a form component.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bkj1665702660842__section_w222ab1b7b1_w223ab1b7_w224ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bkj1665702660842__table_d14576e1_d14577e1_d14578e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Declaration:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger next</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Applies to:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lym1665702585074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lym1665702585074.html\" title=\"A Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in an Entity. This could represent a column in a DBMS table or data that is not stored in the database, such as a derived field or a user interface control. Its associated properties define the way it is stored, its GUI representation, and default behavior.\">Field</a> in form components.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activation:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activated by the structure editor functions ^NEXT_FIELD or ^FIELD (when the direction is Next), after the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">loseFocus</span> trigger completes successfully.\n <p class=\"p\">This trigger is not activated when the cursor is moved with arrow keys or mouse clicks, or by setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default behavior:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Behavior upon completion:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n <p class=\"p\">If <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> is less than zero, the user cannot leave the field. However, the user is free to leave the field in a way that does not activate this trigger, for example, with a structure editor function such as ^PREVIOUS_FIELD or with the cursor keys.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bkj1665702660842__section_w225ab1b7b3_w226ab1b7_w227ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1062606e144\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bkj1665702660842__p_d117662e1_d117663e1_d117664e1\">This trigger can be used to control the prompting\n            sequence of fields. It should not be used for data validation processing because the\n            user can leave the field in a way that does not activate this trigger. For more\n            information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"czd1665702630519.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/czd1665702630519.html\" title=\"Trigger that reacts to a field getting focus in a Form component. It is usually used for user interactions such as prompting the user with a hint message, or modifying the way a field is displayed.\">trigger getFocus (Field)</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wbv1665702600112.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wbv1665702600112.html\" title=\"Trigger that defines what happens after a user successfully leaves a field in a form component.\">trigger loseFocus (Field)</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bkj1665702660842__section_qjq_b1h_fcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1062606e167\">Example: next</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">You can use change the default prompting sequence of fields by setting\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span> to the next appropriate field. The following example\n               prompts for a maiden name if the user enters a gender of ‘F’ (for female):</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"bkj1665702660842__pre_zby_b1h_fcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger next ; Field (of GENDER)\n if (GENDER = \"F\") ; female, so prompt for maidenname\n $prompt = MAIDEN_NAME\n endif\n otherwise, use default prompt sequence\nend; next\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/czd1665702630519.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger getFocus (Field)</a><p>Trigger that reacts to a field getting focus in a Form component. It is usually used for user interactions such as prompting the user with a hint message, or modifying the way a field is displayed.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wbv1665702600112.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger loseFocus (Field)</a><p>Trigger that defines what happens after a user successfully leaves a field in a form component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/umg1665702660913.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger previous</a><p>Trigger that responds to a request for the previous field in a form component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526092\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526092\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger next Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger next Trigger that responds to a request for the next field in a form component. Declaration: trigger next Applies to: Field in form components. Activation: Activated by the structure editor functions ^NEXT_FIELD or ^FIELD (when the direction is Next), after the loseFocus trigger completes successfully. This trigger is not activated when the cursor is moved with arrow keys or mouse clicks, or by setting $prompt . Default behavior: None Behavior upon completion: None If $status is less than zero, the user cannot leave the field. However, the user is free to leave the field in a way that does not activate this trigger, for example, with a structure editor function such as ^PREVIOUS_FIELD or with the cursor keys. Description This trigger can be used to control the prompting sequence of fields. It should not be used for data validation processing because the user can leave the field in a way that does not activate this trigger. For more information, see trigger getFocus (Field) and trigger loseFocus (Field) . Example: next You can use change the default prompting sequence of fields by setting $prompt to the next appropriate field. The following example prompts for a maiden name if the user enters a gender of ‘F’ (for female): trigger next ; Field (of GENDER) if (GENDER = \"F\") ; female, so prompt for maidenname $prompt = MAIDEN_NAME endif otherwise, use default prompt sequence end; next Copy Related Links trigger getFocus (Field) Trigger that reacts to a field getting focus in a Form component. It is usually used for user interactions such as prompting the user with a hint message, or modifying the way a field is displayed. trigger loseFocus (Field) Trigger that defines what happens after a user successfully leaves a field in a form component. trigger previous Trigger that responds to a request for the previous field in a form component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}